; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/form-ontology-loader.fk form-stdlib/line-grammar.fk form-stdlib/bmf-core.fk form-stdlib/bmf-grammar.fk form-stdlib/grammar-loader.fk form-stdlib/shell-grammar.fk form-stdlib/voice-traits.fk form-stdlib/feature-vector.fk form-stdlib/nearest-shape.fk form-stdlib/voice-diarize.fk form-stdlib/shell-exec.fk
;
; fsh-probe — does the body's OWN grep answer, without bash?
;
; The orchestrating mind ran external grep several hundred times on 2026-07-21/22
; while shell-exec.fk's fifteen four-way-proven builtins sat unused. The `fsh`
; front door is blocked (fsh-main's restructure, named 2026-07-03, still open
; 2026-07-17), but the BUILTINS never needed it. This asks one of them a question
; the mind had been asking bash: how many rows does the corpus hold?
;
; Answer shape: sh-bi-grep returns (list stdout exit); with -c the stdout is the
; count and a newline. Returns the count as an int so fkwu can print it.

(do
    (let src (read_file "learn/homecoming-distillation-corpus.fk"))
    (let r (sh-bi-grep (list "-c" "(hdc-row ") src))
    (str_to_int (head r)))
